"title": "5322: gallows",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5322",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A wooden structure, sometimes a tree, used to impale or display a body after death, or for execution by hanging. Those hanged on gallows were deemed to be under God's curse.</p>\n<h2>A gallows used for impalement and display of bodies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:11\">EZR 6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:29\">JOS 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:26\">JOS 10:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:12\">2SA 4:12</a></p>\n<h2>A gallows used for execution</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:9-Esth7:10\">EST 7:9–7:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:23\">EST 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:13\">EST 9:13</a></p>\n<h2>Those hanged on gallows are under God's curse</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:23\">DEU 21:23</a></p>",
